# Antigravity MCP Server Initialization

This plan outlines the steps to configure the [antigravity-mcp-server](file:///home/gonya/antigravity-mcp-server) as the core execution node for the "Phase 5: Migration to MCP".

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be installing `dockerode` to interact with the Docker daemon. Please ensure the user running this server has permissions to access the Docker socket (usually requires being in the `docker` group).

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
- Install `dockerode` and `@types/dockerode`.

### [src/index.ts](file:///home/gonya/antigravity-mcp-server/src/index.ts)
- Implement the MCP Server using `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`.
- Configure `StdioServerTransport` for local communication.
- Register tools: `docker_control` and `gpu_status`.

### `src/tools/docker.ts` [NEW]
- Implement `docker_control` tool.
- Capabilities: List containers, Start/Stop containers, Inspect container.
- Use `dockerode` library.

### `src/tools/ollama.ts` [NEW]
- Implement `gpu_status` tool.
- Check Ollama operational status (e.g., `GET /api/tags`).
- Report model availability as a proxy for GPU readiness.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **Build Verification**: Run `npm run build` to ensure TypeScript compiles without errors.
- **Dry Run**: Run `node dist/index.js` (will likely hang waiting for stdin, but verifies startup). 

### Manual Verification
- The user can verify the server is running by configuring their client (Claude Desktop or VS Code) to point to this server and listing available tools.
